Package org.uma.jmetal.auto.parameter

Class Parameter<T>

java.lang.Object
org.uma.jmetal.auto.parameter.Parameter<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Type of the parameter
Direct Known Subclasses:
CategoricalParameter, IntegerParameter, OrdinalParameter, PositiveDoubleValue, PositiveIntegerValue, RealParameter, StringParameter
public abstract class Parameter<T>
extends java.lang.Object
Abstract class representing generic parameters. Any parameter has a name and a value that is assigned by parsing an array called args which contains sequences of pairs [key, value]. For example, the args field could contain these values: ["--populationSize", "100", "--offspringPopulationSize", "100", "--createInitialSolutions", "random"] Every parameter has a name (such as "populationSize" or "offpspringPopulationSize") and a value that is obtained after invoking the parse() and check() methods. Parameters can be seen a factories of any kind of objects, from single values (e.g., RealParameter to genetic operators (e.g., MutationParameter). A parameter can contain other parameters, so we define three different types of associations between them. We illustrate the associations by using the CrossoverParameter as an example: - global parameter: any crossover has a probability parameter - specific parameter: a SBX crossover has a distribution index as specific parameter - non-configurable parameter: constant parameters needed by a particular parameter The class provides methods for setting and getting these sup-parameters: - addGlobalParameter(Parameter) - addSpecificParameter(String, Parameter)} - addNonConfigurableParameter(String, Object) - getGlobalParameters() - getSpecificParameters() - getNonConfigurableParameter(String) - findGlobalParameter(String) - findSpecificParameter(String)
Author:
Antonio J. Nebro
